<b><font size=2>Original Message<hr>"Why Everquest and not AC/Darktide?"</font></b><br>
Posted by Kyriel  on 12-05-01 at 08:46&nbsp;PM<br>
<blockquote>Why compete in Everquest, a fundamentally PvM game, when Darktide in Asheron's Call has true unlimited and challenging PvP?  Exping a character to the point where it's viable in PvP isn't the same rediculously boring task it is in EQ, and with the final removal of GEAR/speedhack/client hack/etc by Turbine, there are no longer issues of cheats.<P>All the major downsides of AC (poor graphics, limited class selection for PvP) were certainly present in NWN; I don't recall seeing a non-CL/MU KAAOSer.  On the plus side, it has many of the advantages of NWN, from low system requirements to interesting 1v1 and team v team PvP.<P>With Shadowbane most likely a year or more away, there's certainly time.</blockquote><hr><b><font size=2>Table of contents</font></b><hr>
