<b>"RE: Why Everquest and not AC/Darktide?"</b><br>
Posted by J.  on 12-10-01 at 00:15&nbsp;AM<br>
<blockquote>
&gt;NPC manipulation and turn based combat <BR>&gt;are not the be-all end-all <BR>&gt;of PvP.  In my <BR>&gt;opinion, a more twitch based <BR>&gt;scheme is preferable to pure <BR>&gt;turn based, even timed turn <BR>&gt;based. <P>If you ask any MMOG programmer not faking his way through to the next paycheck by his moron employer about the reality of asynchronous client-server architecture, he'll tell you that twitch-based game design is impossible when you've got a server trying to track the movements of 1,000-plus players at once.<P>In other words, can't have Soul Calibre Online, so you better think of something else.<P>&gt;And yeah.. you do need to <BR>&gt;keep exping now and then, <BR>&gt;both to burn vitae and <BR>&gt;to edge closer to the <BR>&gt;exp-chain whored characters.  You <BR>&gt;could of course build your <BR>&gt;own chain, but that would <BR>&gt;require somebody to keep leveling.. <BR>&gt;and KAAOS doesn't have a <BR>&gt;history of inviting in loads <BR>&gt;of carebears to provide them <BR>&gt;with exp. <BR>&gt;<BR>&gt;Logical, at least. <P>Yeah, logical as it relates to why not many people here are interested in AC. Thanks for making the point for them.<P>J.
